                <h1>USCIS Background Check Explained: What Happens After Your Interview</h1>
                <p>After your USCIS interview, the background check process is a crucial step toward obtaining your immigration status. USCIS will review your criminal history, immigration records, and other information. This check can take anywhere from a few weeks to several months. Staying informed and proactive during this phase is essential.</p>
